annotation.TEXT: Okay, I think I got lucky up there...
Done! Now I just gotta wait for the flames to all go off screen, and then the level's cleared!
Yikes!
Okay, last level for today, level 49!
Wow, a stunned shell-less Remilia looks weird and has flashing hair for some reason...
Now for level 42. Yeah, Sanae's got to march all the way over there, but that was unavoidable. At least I can get there practically at warp speed!
BGM: Final Fantasy 6 - The Decisive Battle
Oh, god. This one... will not be so easy. Um... Good luck!
That one was close enough to hit Mario there? Weird, but whatever. I was gonna win anyway, as this doesn't exactly take a miracle to clear.
Level 43...
Reimu, it's your turn, and I expect your deathless streak to come to an end here.
Alright, well that's it for the 40s. Now, let's do the usual path progress checking...
Level 44...
Alright, halfway done with the 40s. Now for level 45...
You can jump on the Sakuyas, but you probably should use a Remilia shell to take out the Sakuya in between the pipes at the very least.
I wanted to go for a 1-up combo here, which Sanae could've used, but I guess the sprite limit wasn't going to allow me to do that. Oh, well.
Ooh, another favorite level of Goron's and Bear's. Quite simply, it's another defeat-them-all level where you gotta hit the ON/OFF switch multiple times.

And now for level 41, which I've pre-positioned Reimu all the way over here for. (Of course, if Sanae had failed level 40, that pre-positioning would've been wasted, but I was betting on a success from Sanae.)
Oh, this one's not so bad. It looks intimidating, but it's actually pretty simple, as you're always going with the flow of the projectiles, and the sprite limit helps you out a bit too.
Oh, I remember this one from Goron50's videos as well. The boss this time is none other than Mario himself! (Or at least a giant head of him.)

I'd like to say I "saw" that one coming, but it actually surprised me, and I just got lucky again. So, yeah. React quickly to the saws at the start, and be aware of the arrow ceilings and random bullets. It's kind of tricky.
We're getting closer and closer, that's for sure!
You start with exactly enough Kisumes to get the job done, and you have to bounce off one of the lower ones to reach the upper one (so don't save the upper one until last, obviously).
Fortunately, Reimu's still working miracles for me here. (Shouldn't that be Sanae's thing?)
So, next time, we do the 50s. Will one of the levels in the 50s drive me totally nuts and/or crash the game? Find out next time! To be continued...
Darn! I thought I was going to pull another miracle here, but I guess I can't get lucky every time...
Man, this just isn't Sanae's day. Reimu, get in there.
BGM: Final Fantasy 4 - Boss Battle (reused again)

Also, don't miss with any of your shots, but fortunately, you really don't have to worry to much about being accurate if you just place the stunned Kisumes on the left "pen" and wait for Mario to run into them.

Heck, yeah! Also, one other thing: Be careful with your movements in this level. I've seen Goron and Bear simply just fall off the level multiple times. (Also, if you aim perfectly, you can squeeze yourself into the slots, making your shell shots gimmes, but that's pretty tricky.)

Your aim's gotta be just right though. If you don't use that trick, then yeah, you have exactly enough weapons to hit the switch the necessary five times, but pulling off this trick gives you some leeway in case you screw up with some of the weapons.
D'oh! And just like that, I wasted two weapons, but I have not actually failed yet! If you're capable of hitting the ON/OFF block yourself, you'll only need to hit the block twice with other things.
And that's it for this level. Don't worry about where you'll land after the victory music starts. You can't be Kaizo trapped by these spiky things.

Now, the objective here is to aim the shells carefully into the slots to take out the Kisumes. One miss, and the level becomes unwinnable. (Note, you can't pass through those white X-blocks, but the shells can.)
BGM: Nintendo World Championships 1990 - Beginning of the Championship
Sanae, do you think you can take level 46?
Ooh, another one of Goron's and Bear's favorite levels. And, thanks to a video by Bear, I know what this song is! (But why has that video been "disliked" so much?)
D'oh! I seriously didn't expect that to happen! Talk about a sneaky, underhanded tactic, taking out your own ally in order to screw me over like that!

The Sakuyas here fortunately don't toy around with time manipulation, and their somewhat infrequent knives aren't terribly fast and will go over your head if you don't jump (but don't let a Sakuya walk into you while you're not jumping, obviously).
Level 47...
Sanae demos: 7
Sanae demos: 6
BGM: Ievan Polkka (reused)
BGM: Sonic the Hedgehog (Game Gear) - Sky Base Zone
Still can't quite reach the upper-right palm tree yet, but I'm sure it'll become accessible in due time.
Just like Staples, "that was easy".
BGM: Zelda: Link's Awakening - Cave
BGM: Zelda: Twilight Princess - Secret Village (reused)
Okay, this one shouldn't be as hard as the last level. It is slippery, but that shouldn't be too big of an issue. Just carefully destroy all of the enemies.

Yeah, way to go, Reimu! Honestly, I'm surprised this level only took me two tries. (But, then again, I passed that earlier pumpkin head level on my first try, and I thought that one would be murder for me at first!)
And just like that, I'm done!
Alright, Sanae, show us your miracle powers in level 48!
Just be careful not to accidentally overshoot the pen completely or clunk two Kisumes together, and this should be fairly easy.
Oh, this one's pretty easy if you know what you're doing.
BGM: Cave Story - Living Waterway
Ooh, I start off with a cape for this one, and it looks like I'm going to have to spin jump off of the fishing Yuyuko to reach the goal moon. Aim carefully...
BGM: Mega Man 3 - Snake Man's Stage
However, this puzzle gives you more tools than you actually need, because you can actually headbutt the ON/OFF block yourself and survive if you move quickly towards a side brick after doing so.
Well, that didn't seem so hard to me, but maybe the game was being nice to me again.
Yo, dudes! It's time for more Hakurei Adventure Mission! Once again, I did a couple of off screen Start+Selects to get the overworld music back and reposition our protagonists. Now for level 40...
Okay, now that I know that the left disco shell can take out the left flying Remilia, I'm just going to sit here and wait for that to happen.
I wonder why that happens to the left one but not the right one? Well, anyway, time to take out the rest of the trash here!
Whoa. I'm still okay. Just try again...
Got lucky up there again, but can I make it down here too?
Maybe you'll get to perform a real miracle next time, Sanae.
BGM: Wonder Boy in Monster World - Final Dungeon
Oh, hey there Sakuya! Okay, so this level isn't too bad actually.
Alright, I'm two-for-two. Can I land the last shot?
Okay, if I aim this Kisume right, I can win right here.
